race.comment: CHESS MASTER (3) took charge before the turn then defied all challengers for a tough maiden win over 1000m at Port Macquarie last time out. Draws a nice gate again so with some natural improvement still to come another big run is on the cards. MONARCH EXPRESS (2) returns from a 14-week spell. Raced well in the early part of last prep without success. Should enjoy a gun run and is right in the picture. MIDWEST PRINCESS (10) raced handy then was a bit too strong for a maiden field over 1000m here last start. Lightly raced and capable of going to this next level. OLIVERSHARE (6) was plain first-up at Ballina but can improve coming back in trip. The sparingly raced ULTIMATE SAY (9) returns from a five-month spell. Opened the maiden campaign with an all-the-way win here at this trip. Perfectly drawn and cannot be underestimated.
